name: Docker
help: Docker is an open platform for developing, shipping, and running applications. Docker enables you to separate your applications from your infrastructure so you can deliver software quickly. With Docker, you can manage your infrastructure in the same ways you manage your applications. By taking advantage of Dockerâ€™s methodologies for shipping, testing, and deploying code quickly, you can significantly reduce the delay between writing code and running it in production.

properties.name: CacheFrom
properties.help: Images to consider as cache sources.

properties.help: Optional parent cgroup for the container.

properties.help: Compress the build context using gzip.

properties.name: CpuPeriod
properties.help: Limit the CPU CFS (Completely Fair Scheduler) period.

properties.name: CpuQuota
properties.help: Limit the CPU CFS (Completely Fair Scheduler) quota.

properties.name: CpusetCpus
properties.help: CPUs in which to allow execution (0-3, 0,1).

properties.name: CpusetMems
properties.help: MEMs in which to allow execution (0-3, 0,1).

properties.name: Iidfile
properties.help: Write the image ID to the file.

properties.name: MemorySwap
properties.help: Swap limit equal to memory plus swap: '-1' to enable unlimited swap.

properties.name: Network
properties.help: Set the networking mode for the RUN instructions during build.

properties.name: NoCache
properties.help: Do not use cache when building the image.

properties.name: Platform
properties.help: Set platform if server is multi-platform capable.

properties.name: Progress
properties.help: Set type of progress output (<c>auto</c>, <c>plain</c>, <c>tty</c>). Use plain to show container output.

properties.name: Pull
properties.help: Always attempt to pull a newer version of the image.

properties.name: Quiet
properties.help: Suppress the build output and print image ID on success.

properties.name: Rm
properties.help: Remove intermediate containers after a successful build.

properties.name: Secret
properties.help: Secret file to expose to the build (only if BuildKit enabled): id=mysecret,src=/local/secret.

properties.name: Squash
properties.help: Squash newly built layers into a single new layer.

properties.name: Ssh
properties.help: SSH agent socket or keys to expose to the build (only if BuildKit enabled) (format: default|<id>[=<socket>|<key>[,<key>]]).

properties.name: Stream
properties.help: Stream attaches to server to negotiate build context.

properties.name: Tag
properties.help: Name and optionally a tag in the 'name:tag' format.

properties.name: Target
properties.help: Set the target build stage to build.

properties.name: Path
properties.help: Path or url where the build context is located.

properties.name: PullImage
properties.help: Whether to execute a <c>docker pull</c> before running the container.

properties.name: DotNetRuntime
properties.help: The .NET Runtime Identifier (RID) to use to publish the build project. For example, linux-x64, linux-arm64, win-x64.

properties.name: BuildCaching
properties.help: Enables caching of the build executable.

properties.name: KeepEnvFile
properties.help: Whether to keep the <c>.env.<target></c> file located under <c>build/bin/<rid></c> after the target is complete.

properties.name: TLSVerify
properties.help: Use TLS and verify the remote.

properties.name: TLSCaCert
properties.help: Trust certs signed only by this CA (default ~/.docker/ca.pem).
